	     Johannesburg - Approximately 100 people have been injured in an apparent passenger train accident near Kroonstad on Thursday morning. ER24 posted on Twitter that the incident occurred on the line between between Hennenman and Kroonstad in the Free State. Initial reports put the number of injured people at around 100.  According to some reports, the train was travelling from Port Elizabeth to Johannesburg, when it apparently collided with a truck and burst into flames.  More to follow. - Are you there?  Send us your eyewitness accounts and photos.    24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  